  "text": "The spots listed are known antigens of H. pylori 26695 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Loci marked with # were identified to be HP0027 by Haas et al. (10) (spots lie in a very dense region). Unknown peaks are reproducible peaks (at least in two of three replicates) that were neither assigned to the main component of the spot nor to a protein close in the dendrogram cluster. None means that all reproducible peaks were assigned to the identified protein in this spot. Those marked with * are minor components that might have influenced the antigenicity of this spot. TIGR, The Institute for Genomic Research; hypoth., hypothetical.",
